#: ../../integration_guide.md:1
msgid "Integration Guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:3
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:5
msgid ""
"STDLIB itself is distributed as a versioned tar archive that can be "
"unpacked to the desired target location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:7
msgid ""
"A consuming project need only source the distributed `stdlib.sh` script "
"to begin using the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:9
msgid "Safely Integrating Trap Signals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:11
msgid ""
"Each time Bash registers a `trap` signal handler, any existing handler is"
" overwritten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:13
msgid ""
"Given this constraint, when integrating STDLIB, take care not to "
"overwrite its trap signal handling by directly registering your own "
"handlers with the `trap` builtin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:15
msgid ""
"Instead, it's recommended to extend STDLIB's trap handling for ERROR and "
"EXIT by using the provided registration functions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:17
msgid "`stdlib.trap.handler.err.fn.register`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:18
msgid "`stdlib.trap.handler.exit.fn.register`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:20
msgid ""
"This allows STDLIB to preserve its own trap handling, while giving "
"consuming projects the ability to safely run one or more custom signal "
"trap handlers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:22
msgid "Embedding STDLIB in a Project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:24
msgid ""
"Embedding stdlib in an existing project may be the easiest method to "
"integrate it quickly.  This is best done in a folder separate and "
"parallel from the source code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:40
msgid "Installing STDLIB Centrally on a System"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:42
msgid ""
"You could also opt to globally install STDLIB so it can be consumed by "
"multiple scripts running on a host machine from a central location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:44
msgid ""
"Typically, this would be done in a `/usr/local/lib/stdlib` or similarly "
"named folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:46
msgid "Enabling Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:48
msgid "External Dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:50
msgid ""
"Depending on how you leverage STDLIB for testing, you'll need to install "
"one or more external tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:52
msgid "bash_unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:54
msgid ""
"This project leverages [bash_unit](https://github.com/bash-"
"unit/bash_unit) under the hood as the test framework."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:56
msgid ""
"Given this constraint, the first step is to install bash_unit on your "
"system, and ensure it's available in PATH."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:58
msgid ""
"It is definitely possible to use other test frameworks instead, but for "
"simplicity right now only bash_unit is officially supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:60
msgid "kcov"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:62
msgid ""
"If you wish to measure code coverage, you'll need to also install "
"[kcov](https://github.com/SimonKagstrom/kcov), and ensure this too is "
"available in PATH."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:64
msgid "Custom 't' Script"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:66
msgid "The 't' script is a callable that is used to invoke test suites."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:68
msgid ""
"To adapt STDLIB to your codebase, you'll need to create a small wrapper "
"script that loads dependencies or sets environment variables in order to "
"establish a \"testing context\" within which the test suites will run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:70
msgid "This project has an example [customized t script](../build/t) that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:71
msgid ""
"exports a custom `_t_runner_custom_execution_context` function to load "
"all the required libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:72
msgid "calls the [stdlib t script](../dist/t) to actually run the test suites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:74
msgid "Presumably your own custom 't' script would perform these same tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:76
msgid "Mocking System"
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:78
msgid ""
"The mocking system records calls in files created by mktemp to simplify "
"the task of mocking dependencies across different processes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../integration_guide.md:80
msgid ""
"If you wish to compartmentalize your system's /tmp folder, "
"containerization is the recommended approach.  This project's own "
"development [leverages this approach](../container.sh) in an attempt to "
"'eat our own dog food'."
msgstr ""

